Installing aws cli on linux os (Centos)

in Lightsail and practice the commands on it. At the end, do not forget to Delete the instance. This is just a test.

1. Install the curl package 
sudo yum install curl -y

2.  Install the unzip package
sudo yum install unzip -y

3. Download the AWS-CLI sources using the curl command
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"

4. Unzip the downloaded file
unzip awscliv2.zip

5. Run the ./aws/install file
sudo ./aws/install

6. Check if AWS CLI is correctly installed in Linux OS
aws --version